name: EA-001-Sócrates
description:
Socrates (470-399 BC) was an ancient Greek philosopher, the first thinker of the trio of ancient Greek philosophers, which included Plato and Aristotle, to lay the philosophical foundations of Western culture. “Know thyself” is the essence of all his teaching. 3/3 with 
10% permanent royalits in the blue print.

Digital Watercolor Vector Illustration made in Adobe Photoshop, 1200x1200px, 200dpi, JPEG
